# "If you change `end` to be the current level of the transient, it seems to
# stop, but in fact the slope is just zero and it still lasts until the duration
# is over." So the output stalls at the current level, but the phase (an
# internal CLOCK, not the normalized position) keeps running to 1, and
# endoftransient fires only when the full duration has elapsed.
# start=0, end=0.5, duration=1 s (tickrate 10). At t5 the output is at 0.25 and
# `end` is set to exactly 0.25: output holds 0.25, phase keeps counting
# 0.6, 0.7 ... 1.0, and eot goes high at t10 (not at t5).
tickrate 10
patch <<<
[transient]
    start          = 0
    end            = I1
    duration       = 1
    output         = O1
    phase          = O2
    endoftransient = O3
>>>
@0 set I1 0.5
@5 expect O1 0.25 tol 1e-4
@5 expect O2 0.5 tol 1e-4
# end -> current level: slope becomes zero, but the transient is NOT finished
@6 set I1 0.25
@6 expect O1 0.25 tol 1e-4
@6 expect O2 0.6 tol 1e-4
@6 expect O3 0
@9 expect O1 0.25 tol 1e-4
@9 expect O2 0.9 tol 1e-4
@9 expect O3 0
# duration elapsed: now it is really over
@10 expect O1 0.25 tol 1e-4
@10 expect O2 1.0 tol 1e-4
@10 expect O3 1
